# No trailing full stop

All visible text on the website — paragraphs, spans, headings, lede props, pull-quote `text` props, `qualifier`, `standfirst`, success messages, checkbox labels, placeholder attributes, and any other user-facing copy — must **not** end with a full stop (period).

Mid-sentence periods within multi-sentence text blocks are fine. Only the **final** period at the very end of a text element or prop value is removed.

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
lede="Each remedy is presented as a scholarly record"
text="Knowledge before commerce. Service before profit"
<p>The institution exists for the next generation</p>

// ❌ Wrong
lede="Each remedy is presented as a scholarly record."
text="Knowledge before commerce. Service before profit."
<p>The institution exists for the next generation.</p>
```

## Scope

- Applies to all JSX/TSX rendered text: props, children, template literals displayed to users.
- Does **not** apply to code comments, metadata `description` fields (SEO), or programmatic strings like error codes.
- Question marks and exclamation marks at the end of text are unaffected — only the period.
